● Good overview. Here's where I think Summit could go from here. Let me organize by impact and effort:

  ---
  High Value, Moderate Effort

  1. Commit & PR management from the UI
  Right now Claude makes changes in a worktree, but there's no way for the user to commit, push, or create a PR from the
  UI. This feels like the natural next step after the changed files panel.

  ┌─────────────────────────────┐
  │  Changed Files        [PR]  │
  │  ─────────────────────────  │
  │  + server.py      +13 -1   │
  │  ~ config.yaml     +2 -0   │
  │                             │
  │  ┌─────────────────────┐   │
  │  │ Commit message...   │   │
  │  │                     │   │
  │  └─────────────────────┘   │
  │  [Commit] [Commit & Push]  │
  │  [Create PR]               │
  └─────────────────────────────┘

  2. Model selector
  You're locked into whatever the SDK defaults to. A dropdown to pick the model (Sonnet vs Opus, etc.) per session would
  give control over cost vs capability.

  3. System prompt / CLAUDE.md editor
  Let users configure the system context per session — "you're working on the Python backend" or "only use TypeScript".
  Could even let them edit a .claude/ config from the UI.

  4. Session branching / merge back
  You have worktrees, but no way to merge results back to main, cherry-pick, or compare branches. A "merge to main" or
  "create PR" button would close the loop.

  ---
  High Value, Lower Effort

  5. Keyboard shortcuts
  Ctrl+N for new session, Ctrl+K for session switcher, Ctrl+Shift+C for changes panel, etc. Power users will want these.

  6. Search across sessions
  As sessions accumulate, finding that one conversation where you solved a specific problem becomes painful. Full-text
  search across messages.

  7. File tree browser
  Show the worktree's file structure in the changed files panel (as a tab). Lets users browse what Claude has access to,
  not just what changed.

  8. Stop/cancel a running query
  There's no abort button right now. If Claude goes on a tangent, you're stuck waiting.

  ---
  Medium Value, Higher Effort

  9. Collaborative editing / live file preview
  Show the file content as Claude edits it in real-time. Think a Monaco editor panel that updates as tool_use events come
  in for Write/Edit operations.

  10. Cost tracking dashboard
  You already have cost_usd per message. Aggregate it — per session, per day, running total. Useful for teams managing
  budgets.

  11. MCP server management
  Configure and toggle MCP servers from the UI instead of config files. Show which servers are connected, their tools,
  health status.

  12. Session templates / starter prompts
  Pre-configured sessions: "Code Review" (with a system prompt focused on reviewing), "Bug Fix" (scoped to debugging),
  "Refactor" (architectural focus). Quick starts.

  ---
  Nice-to-Have / Future

  13. Multi-file diff view — side-by-side or tabbed diffs for all changes at once
  14. Voice input — Web Speech API for hands-free prompting
  15. Image/screenshot paste — Drag & drop images into the chat
  16. Export conversation — Download as markdown, share a link
  17. Undo last Claude action — Git revert of the last commit in the worktree
